<subSubSection type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageNumber="2">
Diagnosis. Distinguished from the two other known South American freshwater sciaenid genera (
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:F85FE3B0-DEB1-4A78-B6EB-E88E243F54A6" class="Diplopoda" family="Platyrhacidae" genus="Pachyurus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Pachyurus Agassiz 1831:125, 127" order="Polydesmida" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Pachyurus</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:B27B431C-FC51-4ABC-B9FC-28F9655026C6" class="Actinopterygii" family="Sciaenidae" genus="Plagioscion" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Plagioscion Gill 1861:82" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Plagioscion</taxonomicName>
) by the following combination of characters: mouth inferior, presence of three mental barbels, the swimbladder with a pair log posterior branches projecting from shorter paired anterior appendages (Fig. 1), and presence of the expanded haemal spine on the first caudal vertebra (Fig. 2). Gender masculine.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection type="discussion">
<paragraph pageNumber="2">
Comments. According to Sasaki (1989), 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:A1A52A20-86AC-4DC1-89BB-A5D1CC1CBBDB" class="Actinopterygii" family="Sciaenidae" genus="Pachypops" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Pachypops Gill 1861:87" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Pachypops</taxonomicName>
is characterized phylogenetically by its swimbladder with a pair of anterior appendages (see Fig. 1), the possession of an unpored median barbel, and the possession of a pair of mental barbels. An unpublished phylogenetic study of South American freshwater sciaenids done by the author of the present paper reveals that the species of 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:A1A52A20-86AC-4DC1-89BB-A5D1CC1CBBDB" class="Actinopterygii" family="Sciaenidae" genus="Pachypops" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Pachypops Gill 1861:87" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Pachypops</taxonomicName>
share not only those synapomorphies listed by Sasaki (1989) but also an expanded haemal spine on the first caudal vertebra (see Fig. 2). These four synapomorphies are assumed to be homoplastic with other perciforms in the final most parsimonious phylogeny.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection type="discussion">
<paragraph pageNumber="4">
Jordan and Eigenmann (1889: 413) assigned 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:D0D45D89-82A0-44EE-875D-56D6DD37C678" class="Diplopoda" family="Platyrhacidae" genus="Pachyurus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Pachyurus Lepipterus adspersus Steindachner 1879:123 [5]" order="Polydesmida" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="adspersus">Pachyurus adspersus Steindachner 1879</taxonomicName>
to the genus 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:A1A52A20-86AC-4DC1-89BB-A5D1CC1CBBDB" class="Actinopterygii" family="Sciaenidae" genus="Pachypops" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Pachypops Gill 1861:87" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="4" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Pachypops</taxonomicName>
. However, despite bearing three mental barbels and six mental pores, 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:D0D45D89-82A0-44EE-875D-56D6DD37C678" class="Diplopoda" family="Platyrhacidae" genus="Pachyurus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Pachyurus Lepipterus adspersus Steindachner 1879:123 [5]" order="Polydesmida" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="adspersus">P. adspersus</taxonomicName>
lacks the expanded haemal spine and the appendages on the swimbladder, which occur in 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:A1A52A20-86AC-4DC1-89BB-A5D1CC1CBBDB" class="Actinopterygii" family="Sciaenidae" genus="Pachypops" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Pachypops Gill 1861:87" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="4" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Pachypops</taxonomicName>
. Casatti (2001) considered 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:D0D45D89-82A0-44EE-875D-56D6DD37C678" class="Diplopoda" family="Platyrhacidae" genus="Pachyurus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Pachyurus Lepipterus adspersus Steindachner 1879:123 [5]" order="Polydesmida" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="adspersus">P. adspersus</taxonomicName>
a member of 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:F85FE3B0-DEB1-4A78-B6EB-E88E243F54A6" class="Diplopoda" family="Platyrhacidae" genus="Pachyurus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Pachyurus Agassiz 1831:125, 127" order="Polydesmida" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Pachyurus</taxonomicName>
as originally proposed by Steindachner. An expanded haemal spine on the first caudal vertebra is also present in some other examined perciforms (the haemulid 
<taxonomicName class="Actinopterygii" family="Haemulidae" genus="Haemulon" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="4" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="steindachneri">Haemulon steindachneri</taxonomicName>
, the polynemid 
<taxonomicName class="Actinopterygii" family="Polynemidae" genus="Polydactylus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="4" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="virginicus">Polydactylus virginicus</taxonomicName>
, and the sciaenids 
<taxonomicName class="Actinopterygii" family="Sciaenidae" genus="Dendrophysa" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="4" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="russelli">Dendrophysa russelli</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName class="Actinopterygii" family="Sciaenidae" genus="Kathala" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="4" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="axillaris">Kathala axillaris</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName class="Actinopterygii" family="Sciaenidae" genus="Plagioscion" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="4" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="auratus">Plagioscion auratus</taxonomicName>
, pers. obser.) but it is interpreted as having been independently derived in these taxa.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageNumber="4">
Based on the barbel morphology 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:B0D8702C-99BE-4E65-926C-A901941132BB" class="Actinopterygii" family="Sciaenidae" genus="Pachypops" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Pachypops cevegei Cervigón 1982:237" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="4" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="cevegei">
Pachypops cevegei 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Cervigón">Cervigon</normalizedToken>
1982
</taxonomicName>
is not a species of 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:A1A52A20-86AC-4DC1-89BB-A5D1CC1CBBDB" class="Actinopterygii" family="Sciaenidae" genus="Pachypops" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Pachypops Gill 1861:87" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="4" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Pachypops</taxonomicName>
, but instead a species of 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:CB92F15C-B6D6-492D-8A48-2271D89872D3" class="Actinopterygii" family="Sciaenidae" genus="Micropogonias" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Micropogonias Bonaparte 1831:170" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="4" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Micropogonias</taxonomicName>
. Therefore, of six nominal species of 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:A1A52A20-86AC-4DC1-89BB-A5D1CC1CBBDB" class="Actinopterygii" family="Sciaenidae" genus="Pachypops" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Pachypops Gill 1861:87" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="4" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Pachypops</taxonomicName>
according to previous authors, two (
<taxonomicName class="Actinopterygii" family="Sciaenidae" genus="Pachypops" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="4" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="adspersus">Pachypops adspersus</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:B0D8702C-99BE-4E65-926C-A901941132BB" class="Actinopterygii" family="Sciaenidae" genus="Pachypops" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Pachypops cevegei Cervigón 1982:237" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="4" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="cevegei">Pachypops cevegei</taxonomicName>
) are not assignable to the genus. The remaining nominal species are discussed below under “Comments” for 
<taxonomicName class="Actinopterygii" family="Sciaenidae" genus="Pachypops" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="4" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="fourcroi">Pachypops fourcroi</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName class="Actinopterygii" family="Sciaenidae" genus="Pachypops" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="4" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="trifilis">Pachypops trifilis</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
